President Biden visited O'Connor Farm in Kankakee, Illinois and spoke about the importance of agriculture and conservation. He highlighted his own experience with farming in Delaware and praised the hard work and dedication of American farmers. The President discussed the impact of climate change on agriculture, particularly in relation to wildfires and droughts, and expressed his commitment to addressing these challenges. He also addressed the ongoing conflict in Ukraine and its impact on global food supplies, emphasizing the role of American farmers in feeding the world. President Biden outlined his administration's efforts to support farmers, including reducing red tape, investing in fertilizer production, and promoting competition in the agricultural industry. He stressed the need to invest in farmers to ensure a secure and affordable food supply for the nation and the world. The President ended his speech by expressing his confidence in the resilience and potential of the American people, emphasizing that the United States can overcome any crisis when united.